xies, HII regions show higher\n$\\log_{10}(F_{70 micron}/F_{12 micron})$ ratios. We find a weak trend of\ndecreasing infrared to ~20 cm flux density ratios with increasing $R_{gal}$, in\nagreement with previous extragalactic results, possibly indicating a decreased\ndust abundance in the outer Galaxy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 17 Aug 2017 16:39:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-09-06"}
